        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S. Robertson</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="89" xml:id="d472fn89">American Commissioner of Executive
                        Headquarters.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">and Brigadier General <persName>Henry A. Byroade</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="90" xml:id="d472fn90">Director of Operations of Executive
                        Headquarters.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-24">24 May
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3053. The Communists continue to make a mockery of team action at the following:
                    Chaoyang Team 26, Chihfeng Team 2, Chengte Team 11, Shih Chia Chuang Team 12,
                    Yungnin Team 31, Hsuchow Teams 4 and 24.</p>
                <p>For your background information separate radio (designated as “Part 2”<note n="91" xml:id="d472fn91">Not found in Department files.</note>) follows
                    transmitting in full message just received in clear from American member Team
                    number 11 Chengte. It is illustrative of the complete frustration now being
                    experienced as result of Communist non-cooperation. Communist branch here
                    apparently powerless to correct situation. Recommend showdown with Chou
                    En-lai.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
